Ask HN: What HTML template engines do you use?
text:
I'm planning on making a small web app using SSR rather than splitting the backend and client work. In researching options for the project (Go based), I've "discovered" that there's a _lot_ more to templates than what I've used in the past (Jinja2 via Django, Flask, and Ansible).

So to the actual web developers here, what template engines do you use and why? I've never worked with compiled templates but they seem interesting, though I don't know their cost/benefit tradeoffs very well yet.

Your choice of language, stack, syntax preference, what-have-you! I'm just genuinely curious about the broader templating ecosystem and workflows.

Ask HN: Any SEs on AS that made a successful switch to a leadership role?
text:
Just curious if there are anyone on the Autism spectrum here that were Software Engineers at some point in the past but now are on leadership/management roles and managing ok! I'm at my wits end as I'm looking for opportunities to grow but none that I can keep hands-on technical.

I'm currently a Senior Engineer with an Asperger's diagnosis, and in the past I had a couple of opportunities where I was a team lead/tech lead but had found it really challenging and came to an embarrassing conclusion (e.g. not all at once: failed/late projects, people leaving the team, friction with my manager...etc). I'm given another opportunity to move to a team lead role in my current job but I'm not sure if I should take it on! Worried I may end up messing it up as I'm not really a social person.

Anyone had similar issues and can provide some tips/suggestions?
